More than a 1000 workers from around Buffalo City Metro converged on the Victoria Grounds in King William s Town yesterday to celebrate May Day. The main speakers at the event included Nehawu general secretary Bereng Soke, sports recreation, arts and culture MEC Pemmy Majodina and former Young Communist League (YCL) leader Buti Manamela.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.